==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Whang
<hw>Whang</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Thong</er>.]</ety> <def>A leather thong.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng. &
Colloq. U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whang</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Whang
<hw>Whang</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To beat; thrash; bang;
also, to throw, hurl, or fling about, violently.</def> <mark>[Scot. &
Dial. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To slice, esp. in large pieces; to chop.</def>
<mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whang</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Whang
<hw>Whang</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A blow; whack.</def>
<mark>[Dial. or Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A large piece or slice; chunk.</def> <mark>[Scot. &
Dial. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Formerly, a house-cleaning party.</def>
<mark>[Local, U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whangdoodle</ent>⟦br⟧
